## 4. The Hand Feel Experience

- Impact Sensation
    - Hardness Words: Crisp, medium-hard, highly energized.
    - Feedback: Very clear and communicative. You know exactly when you've hit the sweet spot.
    - Hold vs. Release: Favors quick release. The dwell time is strictly dependent on the topsheet; the sponge wants to eject the ball rapidly.
    - Dwell Time: Moderate. It feels slightly shorter than traditional 47.5 rubbers due to the high catapult effect.

- Sound/Click
Produces a loud, satisfying metallic click on impact, very reminiscent of the speed-glue era, which is highly confidence-inspiring.

